  "agent_type": "developer",
  "description": "Blocked reason: state.py line 446 lazily imports format_detail_panel from render.py (comment: \"lazy import to avoid circular dependency\"), while render.py imports DETAIL_SECTION_*, EXECUTION_HISTORY_DISPLAY_LIMIT, and formatting helpers from state.py at the top level. This is a logical circular dependency that violates the acceptance criterion \"without cycles.\" Fix: relocate the shared constants/helpers out of state.py into tree.py or a new constants.py so render.py can import them without creating a cycle back to state.\n\nRemaining work: The state \u2194 render circular dependency must be resolved. Recommended: move the constants and formatting helpers that render.py imports from state.py (DETAIL_SECTION_*, EXECUTION_HISTORY_DISPLAY_LIMIT, _format_block, _format_duration_ms, _format_list, _value_or_dash) into tree.py or a new constants.py so render.py no longer depends on state.py at all, eliminating the cycle without lazy imports.",
